Q. Marcio Crispo] Statius Murcus is mentioned by Appian (B.C. iv, 58),who says that Marcius Crispus came from Bithynia with three legions to help Statius Murcus in Syria against Bassus. On the arrival of Cassius (c. 59), Bassus’ army came over to him, and he took the armies of Murcus and Crispus, who voluntarily gave them up and in obedience to the decree of the se- nate.
